                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Kingston, Jamaica</placeName>\n                                        <date>14<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> November 5610</date>.</p>\n                              <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">My dear Sir,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">I avail myself of the present favorable<lb/>\n                                        opportunity of replying to your welcome communication\n                                                  <persName>Dr Glamorgan</persName>,<lb/> and also\n                                        of acknowledging the receipt of a Parcel containing<lb/>\n                                        Four sets of the present volume of the “Occident” to the\n                                                  <date>October</date> No,<lb/> less one copy of No\n                                        4. I have duly delivered them to the Gentlemen,<lb/> on\n                                        whom, thro a little delicacy, I have not yet called for\n                                        the<lb/> amount of subscription, but I intend doing so next\n                                        week, and<lb/> handing over the same to <persName>Mr A C\n                                                  Peixotto</persName>, your agent in this<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>Island</placeName>.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">Permit me to reiterate the high<lb/> sense I\n                                        entertain of your kindness and friendly feeling in\n                                        furnishing<lb/> me with the information requested of\n                                        vacancies in congregations<lb/> in the <placeName>United\n                                                  States</placeName>, requiring Hazanim. On mature\n                                        reflection, it<lb/> is quite evident to me, that great\n                                        (perhaps insurmountable)<lb/> difficulties must necessarily\n                                        arise, in the endeavor to obtain a<lb/> situation in\n                                                  <placeName>America</placeName>, unless the\n                                        applicant be on the spot; to<lb/> give satisfactory proofs\n                                        of his capability &amp;c. Notwithstanding<lb/> the\n                                        confidence I entertain, that I would stand a <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">very fair</hi><lb/> chance of\n                                        gaining the approval of any respectable <add>קהלה</add> and\n                                        that<lb/> the documentary recommendations which I could\n                                        bring in testimony<lb/> of competency, position, and\n                                        character, would be such as any<lb/> individual would be\n                                        proud of possessing, still I must freely<lb/> admit, that it\n                                        would be nevertheless advisable, if I could present<lb/>\n                                        myself to the congregation amongst whom I desire to\n                                        dwell,<lb/> and then and there afford them the means of\n                                        judging for themselves<lb/>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">at present</hi> I cannot do this. My\n                                        engagements in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName> will<lb/> not\n                                        be at an end till the <date>1<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi>\n                                                  May</date> next. When that period<lb/> arrives, I\n                                        will then be in a position to solicit your friendship<lb/>\n                                        substantially, as (with God's Blessing) the opportunity may\n                                        be<lb/> afforded me of a personal acquaintance with\n                                        yourself, and other<lb/> Gentlemen interested in Jewish\n                                        Affairs.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p38p5vw3q/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
